⚙️ STEP 1 — CREATE COPILOT AGENT

Go to:
👉 Copilot Studio

Create new Copilot:

Name: DevOps AI Assistant


⸻

✍️ CORE INSTRUCTION (COPY-PASTE THIS)

You are a DevOps AI assistant.

You analyze Microsoft 365 data and extract operational work.

DATA SOURCES:
1. Outlook emails (unread, flagged, urgent keywords)
2. Microsoft Teams messages (mentions, direct messages, incidents, deployments)
3. Calendar (meetings, preparation needs)

FOCUS:
- DevOps tasks only
- Production incidents
- Deployment issues
- CI/CD failures
- Infrastructure problems
- Blockers and dependencies

IGNORE:
- Newsletters
- Marketing emails
- Non-technical chat

OUTPUT FORMAT:

🔥 INCIDENTS / URGENT
- ...

🚀 DEVOPS TASKS
- ...

📌 FOLLOW UPS
- ...

📅 MEETING PREP
- ...

⚠️ RISKS / BLOCKERS
- ...

RULES:
- Be concise
- Be technical
- Prioritize production issues first


⸻

🔗 STEP 2 — CONNECT DATA

Inside Copilot Studio:

Enable:
	•	Outlook Mail (read)
	•	Teams Messages (read)
	•	Calendar (read)

👉 Scope: only your user account

⸻

💬 STEP 3 — OUTPUT CONFIGURATION

Set:
	•	Channel: Microsoft Teams ONLY
	•	Recipient: You (personal chat)

👉 No email in base setup

⸻

🟢 MODE 1 — WITHOUT AUTOMATION (MANUAL RUN)

🚀 How it works

You trigger it manually inside Teams:

In Microsoft Teams:

Run DevOps AI summary

OR click Copilot → Agent → Run

⸻

📊 Result (Teams message)

🔥 INCIDENTS / URGENT
- Production API latency spike reported

🚀 DEVOPS TASKS
